What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Pretty standard French course, with an emphasis on reading and seeing some (actually very interesting) French books and films. Take it with Professor Burton, she is a wonderful, wonderful teacher who makes what could be a boring course always interesting.
This course is very challenging if you haven't gotten your French to a rather proficient level. That said, I still feel as if it helped me strengthen my language skills a good deal.
The French department at Yale is very well organized, you will get better at French.
Pretty basic grammar lessons- subjunctive, conditional phrases, etc. Homework is pretty easy but time consuming. Also, the films are pretty good.

Its L3. You most likely either need or want to take it, and in either case this review will not matter to you. That said, Mme. Burton is awesome, and I cannot imagine a better professor to take French with at Yale. The books are also really morbid.
